<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="V" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Vault1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Vault,</orth> subst. 1) an arched roof; used of the sky: <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.259" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 259</bibl>.<lb />2) a room with an arched roof; as a cellar: <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.247" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 247</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.143" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 2, 44</bibl> (<emph>sounded like a cannon in a vault;</emph> cf. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.124" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 124</bibl>. The surreptitious Qq and M. Edd. <emph>like a clamour</emph> etc.). <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 101</bibl>. a repository for the dead: <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.111" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 33</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 20</bibl>, <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 86</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 86</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 86</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 86</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>